The evidence with the title 'Medical bills cause 62 percent of bankruptcies ' says Jan 5, 2012  ... Sixty - two percent of all bankruptcies filed in 2007 were tied to medical expenses. ... Using identical definitions in 2001 and 2007 , the share of bankruptcies attributable to medical problems rose by 49.6 % . ... Income loss due to illness also was common , but nearly always coupled with high medical bills . 
